cs.DS, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CC, cs.DL

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the development of a new data structure for pattern search.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper applies innovations from the field of inverted indexing and document retrieval to compressed pattern search.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is another possibility as the paper mentions applied use-cases derived from natural language processing.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a potential category as the paper discusses tradeoff options in indexed pattern search.
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the standard Pizza&Chili methodology and files, which are commonly used in digital library research.
